  "text": "The construction can be generalized to handle start and goal configurations in G and/or P by adding special nodes into the graph. To handle configurations in P, we can add a grasp class index 0 to the graph. For example, in the above example of the box, we will obtain 6 new nodes, (1, 0), (2, 0) , . . . , [CITATION_1] 0) . These nodes are connected to all other nodes with the same placement class. Note, however, that there are no horizontal edges between them since it is not possible to travel directly from one placement class to another in P. To handle configurations in G, we can add a placement class index 0, similarly to the previous case.",
